{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Brownie","content":["Line a rectangular cake pan (approx. 12 in. x 8 in.) with parchment and set aside.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and melt <nobr>4 min\/120°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place butter into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>1 min\/100°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sugar and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Mix <nobr>2 min\/speed 4<\/nobr> while adding eggs and reserved chocolate through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add flour and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer batter into prepared cake pan, spread out evenly with spatula and freeze for 2 hours. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 350°F. Remove brownie batter from freezer and bake 20 minutes (350°F). Remove from oven and flatten slightly with a spatula so all brownies are equal in height. Allow to cool while you make the ganache."]},{"title":"Ganache","content":["Place cream and light corn syrup into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>4 min\/160°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add chocolate and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Allow ganache to cool until firm enough to place into a piping bag. Transfer ganache to a piping bag with a flat piping tip. Refrigerate 20–25 minutes to firm. Cut brownies into 20 pieces and decorate by piping a ribbon of ganache on top. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Brownie","content":["7 oz chocolate (64% cacao) in pieces or chips","10 oz unsalted butter, room temperature, in pieces","12 oz sugar","4 - 5 large eggs, (approx. 7.5 oz)","6 ½ oz all-purpose flour"]},{"title":"Ganache","content":["12 oz organic heavy whipping cream","4 ½ oz light corn syrup or liquid gluclose","11 ½ oz chocolate (64% cacao) in pieces or chips"]}],"id":"r110070","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-y3b3FtNC-Xo\/XZWfg0OzZuI\/AAAAAAAAfFs\/4mwpcfOfDS4RwG2WDASNcB6ipV-PxsAEgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wCB2te-bCSFXIBhs.png","title":"Chocolate Ganache Brownie","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"19 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"57 g","calories":"1701 kJ \/ 405 kcal"},"usefulItems":"icing spatula, piping bag and tip, cake pan, rectangular (approx. 12 in. x 8 in.), freezer, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If using chocolate blocks or bars, cut into small pieces and place into mixing bowl and chop <nobr><strong>10 sec\/speed 7<\/strong>.<\/nobr>","Instead of piping ganache onto each piece of brownie, frost the whole brownie with ganache and cut into 20 pieces.","Ganache is rich and decadent which is great for parties, but for a quick treat, skip the ganache and pack up your brownies to go.","If you do not have a piping bag, use a gallon zip lock bag. Once the ganache is inside simply cut off a small piece of the corner and pipe your frosting."],"basicInfo":["advanced","30m","3h","20 portions"]}